t5523.text: You have urged Victorians to avoid buying into the hype, but your behaviour not only fuels public concerns, it completely undercuts the trust Victorians have in Medical Professionals - our most important frontline defence to the virus. [END THREAD]

t5524.text: The failure to ring-fence specialised testing and isolation facilities and centralise care and control since initial diagnoses in Victoria has in effect been a reason for increased proliferation of the virus across Victorian society.

t5525.text: In respect of the Government’s response, your ambition to keep the reproduction rate to under one person in the near future is almost impossible to achieve given the number of undiagnosed people that are likely to have contracted the virus that we are unaware of.

t5526.text: With approximately 10-20% of all cases likely requiring hospitalisation, what certainty can you give the community that the already over-stretched health system can handle this increased burden? Your track record thus far doesn’t leave much room for hope….

t5527.text: ... (unless the case definition is broadened to incite increased testing across the community).

t5528.text: For the next 3-to-4 weeks, the similarity of the symptom profiles for COVID-19 and the common flu will see some patients with stronger immunity contract the virus without necessarily being tested for and diagnosed with it...

t5529.text: The virus is now being transmitted via human-to-human means in the community and infecting those that fail to meet the case definition for a suspected COVID-19 case.

t5530.text: - This means that those potentially infected with COVID-19 have likely attended GPs, coming into contact with immunocompromised people, staff etc - when they could have been triaged through the very same specialist testing centres that you have only (belatedly) opened up y/day.

t5531.text: ... Victorian society through most of January, all of February and up to now given the lack of specialised, isolated testing and treatment facilities in the Public Health system.

t5532.text: - Emerging evidence suggests that the incubation period can be anywhere between 2 and 21 days. Patients are likely still infectious whether they are symptomatic or not - therefore posing a risk to...

t5533.text: The first of Victoria’s coronavirus screening clinics opened y/day - arguably four weeks too late. Here’s why: - Of the cases that have been identified, we know that the transmission through Asia and into Australia has been occurring since mid-January (at the very least).

t5534.text: Whilst we are talking about facts, how about discussing the very late, incompetent and poorly structured response that you have led on this issue.

t5535.text: Now this Doctor will probably have a protracted notification and investigation raised into them which will cause undue stress, presumably leave some of their patients in limbo and ultimately end with no action as there is no contravention of their Code of Conduct.

t5536.text: You noted that she referred this particular matter to AHPRA. Other than for PR reasons, why exactly? Who would have thought that people, including Doctors, get sick.

t5537.text: - Unless the Doctor had been diagnosed with pneumonia (he hadn’t), or had visited a country that was higher risk than the USA (clearly not), the Doctor had no reason to meet the specific COVID-19 self isolation obligations for Health Care Workers.

t5538.text: - Consequently, how could the Doctor have known to self-isolate if there was no reason to suspect a coronavirus diagnosis? - Are doctors with a few sniffles or a runny nose now expected to be put into self-isolation?

t5539.text: - A suspected case is only such when they meet both the epidemiological criteria and clinical (symptom) profile. - The Doctor travelled through the USA. USA is not considered to be a country that poses a risk of transmission.

Unafraid and unashamed, you showed us how to speak up; you made this city a better, fairer place for everyone. https://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/gender/women-have-been-discounted-or-erased-as-city-shaping-leaders-20200307-p547tp.html … #IWD2020
